SETTLEMENT PATTERN EVOLUTION
Spatial Dynamics of Human Communities Across Time
================================================================================

DEFINITION
----------
Settlement pattern evolution = long-term changes in the spatial arrangement,
density, form, size hierarchy, and interconnectedness of human dwellings and
communities across a landscape.

A "settlement pattern" is the observable distribution of sites (camps, hamlets,
villages, towns, cities) and the networks linking them. Studying its evolution
tracks how those distributions shift through time via regional survey, remote
sensing (LiDAR, satellite), dating, and landscape analysis.

CORE SETTLEMENT PATTERNS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. DISPERSED / ISOLATED
   Individual dwellings or farmsteads scattered widely.
